&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vaco by Highspring is seeking a strategic, results-driven Director of Leadership Recruiting to lead the identification, attraction, assessment, and hiring of top leadership talent for the Talent Solutions business. Reporting to the Chief People Officer and taking direction from the President and Executive Partners, this role is responsible for recruiting senior leaders, including Executive Partners, Managing Partners, and line-of-business leadership roles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate brings deep experience in executive and leadership search, talent acquisition strategy, and internal talent partnership. This individual will serve as a trusted advisor to Vaco sales, recruiting, HR, and executive leadership, leading high-impact searches that strengthen the leadership bench, support growth, and ensure leaders hired into the business align with Vaco’s culture, performance expectations, values, and long-term business goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead full-cycle recruitment for leadership-level positions across the Talent Solutions organization, including Executive Partners, Managing Partners, and line-of-business leadership roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Chief People Officer, President, Executive Partners, HR leaders, and business leaders to align leadership recruiting priorities with workforce planning, succession planning, and business growth needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute a leadership recruiting strategy to attract high-performing talent from the talent solutions, workforce solutions, and professional services sectors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong pipelines of passive leadership candidates for key and future hiring needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct structured, consistent candidate evaluation focused on leadership capability, industry experience, business impact, cultural alignment, and potential for long-term success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion equitable and inclusive hiring practices by supporting diverse sourcing strategies, consistent interview processes, and objective candidate evaluation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and drive leadership search processes from intake through offer negotiation, ensuring clear search strategy, stakeholder alignment, timely feedback, and smooth onboarding transitions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise hiring leaders on talent market trends, competitor intelligence, compensation benchmarks, and candidate availability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a high-touch candidate experience for senior-level talent throughout the recruitment process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain recruiting metrics and reporting related to leadership hiring, pipeline health, time-to-fill, quality of hire, stakeholder experience, and hiring outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate search documentation, candidate data, and pipeline activity in the applicant tracking system and related recruiting tools to support transparency, reporting, and process discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously improve leadership recruitment processes, assessment methods, and employer branding strategies to strengthen the company’s ability to attract top talent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support internal mobility and leadership succession efforts by ensuring internal candidates are considered through a fair, transparent, and consistent process when appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the organization externally through networking, industry associations, referrals, and targeted outreach to build awareness of leadership opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Business, Human Resources, Organizational Development, or related field preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of recruiting experience, with significan

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Highspring is a global professional services firm, headquartered in Brentwood, Tennessee. The company delivers integrated solutions across consulting, managed services, and talent solutions, helping organizations align strategy, execution, and talent to drive business outcomes. Highspring operates from more than 50 offices across the United States and continues to expand its global delivery capabilities through onshore, nearshore, and offshore models.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director, Technical Accounting will serve as a key financial leader responsible for overseeing the organization’s technical accounting function, ensuring compliance with U.S. GAAP, and internal policies. This role provides authoritative guidance on complex accounting issues, leads the preparation of technical accounting memos, and supports financial reporting, audit readiness, and policy development. This role requires a hands-on leader with experience in a fast-paced, private equity-backed environment, preferably within consulting, professional services, or staffing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate combines strong technical accounting expertise with the ability to build scalable processes, lead high-performing global teams, and partner cross-functionally to support growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Reporting &amp;amp; Compliance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the preparation of monthly, quarterly, and annual financial statements in accordance with GAAP/IFRS which would include preparation of Balance Sheet, Income Statement and Statement of Cash Flows and Stockholders Equity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure timely and accurate financial reporting monthly across multiple global entities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure timely and accurate quarterly bank compliance reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage audits and regulatory compliance across jurisdictions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and enforce internal controls and accounting policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain accounting policies and procedures aligned with evolving standards and business needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Global Accounting Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead day-to-day accounting functions including revenue recognition, lease accounting and fixed asset accounting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee consolidation of international subsidiaries, including foreign currency considerations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure proper accounting for complex staffing revenue streams (e.g., time &amp;amp; materials, fixed price, direct hire) and intercompany transactions both across geographies and revenue streams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams (Finance, Legal, Tax, FP&amp;amp;A) to assess accounting implications of business initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Private Equity Reporting &amp;amp; Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with executive leadership and private equity stakeholders on financial reporting and performance metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support board reporting, lender compliance, and covenant reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with M&amp;amp;A activities including due diligence, integration, divestiture and corresponding accounting treatment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Improvement &amp;amp; Systems&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the quality and integrity of supporting schedules and workpapers, ensuring they are accurate, well‑controlled, and presented at a level suitable for external audit and executive review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and scale accounting processes to support cleanup of end-to-end accounting treatment from rapid growth and global expansion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;WordSection1&quot;&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;The EHR Manager – Tier 2 is a key member of PivotPoint&#39;s Tier 2 Managed Service Division, responsible for day-to-day management of the Tier 2 Analysts. &amp;nbsp;Serving as an HR manager, this role provides oversight to managed services clients and staff.&amp;nbsp; The ideal candidate will have worked as an EHR analyst, is adaptive to constant change, has experience building teams, monitoring team performance, and customer concerns in a fast-paced and demanding environment. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary with full benefits including medical, dental, vision, 401k, PTO, and more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Occasional after-hours, weekend, and holiday work may be required in this role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;WordSection2&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Roles and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interviews, hires, coaches, and provides training to employees to maintain high customer service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluates employee performance with key metrics (SLA’s, customer feedback, ticket throughput, project milestones).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Approves PTO and timesheets for payroll.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducts effective resource planning to maximize the productivity of resources (people, technology etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains and improves operations by assisting employees with best practices; conducting company lunch and learns; team meetings (including one on ones) with employees; identifying and resolving conflict; preparing and conducting action plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to be 10% billable as a technical lead, project manager, or fill in analyst gaps as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains the on-call schedule, ensuring adequate coverage at all times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Works with the team to oversee client projects and upgrades, including client check-in, meetings, and progress reports.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Works with team leads to conducts quality audits of application analysts ticket work, ensuring established benchmarks are being exceeded and feedback is provided to analysts in monthly one on one sessions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Builds strong relationships with clients, direct reports, and internal PPC team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leads select EHR projects, provides effective project management and drives successful outcomes including monthly progress reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to assist the sales and delivery team with scoping future work, interviewing and providing statement of work documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills and Abilities&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have a strong personal drive for leading, delivering great customer service and thriving in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate knowledge of management principals, healthcare policies, procedures, information systems, Microsoft products and related IT systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certified in core application, additional certifications in ITIL, PMP, MBA are a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lead difficult conversations, analyze data, present the data and make decisions based on the data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication, management, interpersonal and leadership skills required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced conflict resolution skills required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of performance evaluation and customer service metric&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational and leadership skills with problem-solving ability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Education and Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active Epic Certification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree and/or equivalent work experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 5 years of related experience&lt;/li&

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Highspring is looking for an AI leader to help turn AI opportunity into measurable business impact. This role will serve as the connective tissue between business leaders, functional teams, technology partners, and development resources to identify, prioritize, define, and coordinate the implementation of AI-enabled solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will bring structure and momentum to our internal AI efforts. The Enterprise AI Portfolio Lead will manage the intake and prioritization of AI use cases, define business requirements and success criteria, coordinate cross-functional delivery, and help ensure solutions are adopted, measured, and scaled appropriately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate for this role is a hands-on business-minded transformation leader who can operate in ambiguity, ask the right questions, translate business needs into clear requirements, and partner effectively with technical teams to move solutions from idea to implementation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AI Use Case Intake and Portfolio Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and manage a centralized process for evaluating internal AI opportunities across the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain visibility into AI pilots, active builds, and proposed use cases across teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with business and functional leaders to understand opportunities, pain points, workflow gaps, and desired outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run the operating cadence of an AI steering group by preparing materials, recommendations, prioritization inputs, and decision points&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish AI governance: usage standards, data and IP safeguards, and build vs. buy decisioning in partnership with IT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Business Requirements and Solution Definition&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate broad AI ideas into clearly defined use cases, business requirements, user stories, workflow maps, and success criteria&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define minimum viable pilots and phased implementation plans to test, learn, and scale responsibly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prioritization and Roadmap Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain a prioritization framework for internal AI initiatives based on business value, feasibility, data readiness, risk, scalability, strategic alignment, and resource requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend which use cases should be prioritized for pilot, rollout, discovery, or deprioritization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain a roadmap of initiatives, including timelines, owners, dependencies, and expected outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track progress, risks, blockers, decisions, and dependencies across the AI portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cross-functional Delivery Coordination and Measurement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the bridge between business stakeholders, IT, data teams, technology vendors, security, operations, and functional owners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate discovery, requirements, development, testing, feedback, launch, and post-launch optimization for approved initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define success metrics for each initiative before build begins, including adoption, time savings, quality improvement, revenue impact, cost reduction, risk reduction, or employee experience outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor adoption and performance after launch and recommend improvements, expansion, or sunsetting when appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help build organizational confidence in AI by focusing on practical, measurable, high-value use cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At a minimum, you will have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in business transformation, consulting, product management, operations, technology implementat

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This Human Resources Business Partner is responsible for being a strategic business partner to Highspring’s Talent Solutions business unit. They will provide support to US employees by overseeing HR systems, navigating employee relations, ensuring compliance with local law and regulations, and engaging with employees to help fulfill Highspring’s employer value proposition. This is a contract role working 40 hours/week.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Job Functions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential function satisfactorily. The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skills, and abilities required.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Impact&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a trusted advisor to leaders across Talent Solutions, providing guidance on organizational design, workforce planning, and leadership effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide performance management guidance to leadership (e.g. coaching, counseling, career development, disciplinary actions); focus on improving work relationships, building morale, and creating retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create processes and solutions in partnership with leadership which support a positive employee environment through effective communications, policies, and practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and resolve employee relations issues. Conduct effective, thorough, and objective investigations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain in-depth knowledge of legal requirements related to day-to-day management of employees, reducing legal risks, and ensuring regulatory compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify strategies to increase employee performance and change readiness while designing metrics to track the effectiveness of programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze trends and metrics on turnover in partnership with HR leaders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with HR leaders on strategic and operational HR projects and programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The above statements describe the general nature and level of work only. They are not an exhaustive list of all&amp;nbsp;required responsibilities, duties, and skills. Other duties may be added, or this description amended at any time.&amp;nbsp;Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable qualified individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
